  - Combat-Action=Heterodoxy And Deviation=‘And Ye Shall Be as Gods’
---
\'Lest I should be exalted,’ he says (II. Cor. xii, 7), ‘there was given me a
sting of my flesh, an angel of Satan.’ O poison, which is not cured save by
poison!  ‘There was given me a sting of my flesh, an angel of Satan, to
buffet me!’ The head was beaten lest the head should be exalted. O antidote,
which is made, as it were, from a serpent and therefore is called theriacal
For that serpent persuaded to pride. ‘Eat, and you shall be as gods’
(Gen. iii. 5). This is the persuasion of pride; whereby the devil fell,
thereby he cast down.  Justly therefore the serpent’s poison is healed by
the serpent.
